---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="About Naees" description="About Naees, NaeesWrites, secure contact, and Haku the co-author." pathname="/about/">
  <section class="page-hero shell page-hero--with-mark">
    <p class="eyebrow">about</p>
    <h1>Naees builds a public notebook for security work, writing, and useful edge cases.</h1>
    <p class="lede">I write as Naees. NaeesWrites is the blog: a place for security research notes, technical essays, and the occasional personal artifact that keeps the site human.</p>
    <img class="ghost-mark" src={`${base}assets/kittenwiz_logo.webp`} alt="" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
  </section>

  <section class="shell dossier">
    <div class="dossier__panel">
      <h2>Focus areas</h2>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li>Web application security and authorization failures</li>
        <li>Identity, access, and account-boundary mistakes</li>
        <li>Cloud exposure, misconfiguration, and practical attack paths</li>
        <li>Security automation, scripts, notes, and reproducible methodology</li>
        <li>Clear writing: turning confusing systems into readable explanations</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="dossier__panel dossier__panel--dark">
      <h2>Working style</h2>
      <p>I like small clues, boring logs, and the parts of systems that everyone assumes are already handled. The site is designed as a field desk: case files when there is research, essays when there is a lesson, and secure contact when the conversation should not be public.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="shell haku-card">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">co-author / morale officer</p>
      <h2>Haku keeps incident response grounded.</h2>
      <p>Haku does not write the posts, but provides excellent review coverage by sleeping nearby, interrupting long debugging sessions, and reminding the operator to leave the terminal.</p>
      <p class="muted">Status: on duty, probably asleep. Clearance: treats required.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="haku-card__images">
      <img src={`${base}assets/haku.webp`} alt="Haku" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
      <div class="mini-dossier">
        <span>canine division</span>
        <strong>review protocol</strong>
        <p>Sniff anomalies. Interrupt tunnel vision. Enforce walks before overfitting the theory.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="shell contact-block">
    <div>
      <p class="eyebrow">secure contact</p>
      <h2>Open to collaboration and security engagement.</h2>
      <p>For sensitive correspondence, use the PGP key. For quick contact, email is listed in the footer and the keys page includes the current fingerprint.</p>
    </div>
    <a class="button button--primary" href={`${base}keys/`}>View keys and contact</a>
  </section>
</Layout>
